<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910717-0019</DOCNO><DOCID>910717-0019.</DOCID><HL>   Marketing Brief -- Telxon Corp.:   Hand-Held Scanner Systems   To Be Supplied to Nielsen</HL><DATE>07/17/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   DNB TLXN</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)INDUSTRIAL andamp; COMMERCIAL SERVICES, LEASING, CLEANING (ICS)INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL SERVICES (SVC)</IN><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)OHIO (OH)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Telxon Corp., Akron, Ohio, said it received a $9 millioncontract to supply handheld scanner computer systems to aunit of Nielsen Marketing Research USA.   The systems will be used in households to collect dataabout shopping activities. Purchase information, includingbrand, size, flavor, price and quantity, will be transmittedweekly from homes via telephone to Nielsen for analysis. Theinformation will then be used by manufacturers, retailers andother companies.</LP><TEXT>   Telxon said the new system replaces a 10-market local IDcard panel now found in grocery stores. This system allowsdata to be collected directly from households rather than thestores, providing a better picture of U.S. purchasingbehavior, Telxon officials said.   Some of the households will be equipped with TV meters toalso capture TV-viewing habits. That information, combinedwith the purchase information, will tell packaged-goodsmakers more about the effectiveness of advertising, Telxonsaid.   Nielsen Marketing Research is part of Dun andamp; BradstreetCorp. Telxon makes portable hand-held computer systems.</TEXT></DOC>